President Trump hosted a lunch with leaders from several African countries, including Côte d’Ivoire, Ethiopia, Ghana, Guinea, Namibia, Nigeria, Senegal, Uganda, and South Africa. He expressed his desire to extend economic partnerships and promote self-reliance and job creation in Africa. Trump acknowledged Africa's tremendous business potential and encouraged American firms to invest in the continent. He also emphasized the importance of health initiatives and peace, partnering with African countries and organizations to combat violence, terrorism, and humanitarian crises. Trump discussed the ongoing violence in South Sudan and the Congo, and expressed his commitment to providing humanitarian assistance. He mentioned the security threat posed by North Korea and stressed the importance of implementing United Nations sanctions. Trump concluded by praising Africa's potential and expressing his eagerness to discuss the challenges and opportunities facing the continent.